                    "company": "Agro Fair Europe B.V.",
                    "description": "We work with more than 5000 small farmers in a cooperative company. Fairtrade banana suppliers in various Latin-American have a direct say and share in the company  through the Cooperative of Producers of AgroFair (CPAF) b.a. \nAs the CEO, I am leading the Executive Board and Management Team, and responsible for the results of the company. I am accountable to the General Assembly of Shareholders, composed of the Producer Cooperative and a number of ethical investors. The company has a Supervisory Board of three, which meets four times per year with the Executive Board.\n\nThe main achievements of the past years were to make the company more agile and focused, while at the same time providing more services to the producers and increase the volume traded in the interest of the producers. Over the past years, the sales almost doubled from \u20ac 50 to more than \u20ac 90 million.  We started a support organisation close to the producer cooperatives in Panama, Ecuador and Peru, to provide (online) training to indivudal farmers and quality support. Big data and machine learning helps us reduce quality problems. We find sustainability very important: we invested in a plastic recycling factory in Peru, together with partners and producers. We launched the first carbon neutral banana of the Southern Hempisphere, while we work on closing the living wage gap, and measure and reduce the impact of plant protection agents.\nOur customers are large supermarket chains in Europe, South-Korea and New Zealand. \n\nSubsidiary AgroFair Projects B.V. helps disseminate knowledge and experience we have gathered over our 25 year existence and make this available to governments, univiserities and cooperatives in Sub-Saharan Africa and South-East Asia.",
